A physicist has harnessed the power of X-rays to create a stunning series of artworks which reveal animals and plants in an incredible new light .

Arie va n't Riet , 66 , from Bathmen in the Netherlands , began X-raying flowers as a means to teach radiographers and physicians how the machine worked .

